      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Maidens don't come much plainer than this. FARNESINA (2) is back from a 19-week spell for the Munce stable. Ran a couple of respectable races in town in the maiden campaign although never threatened. Two recent trials should have her ready to run a forward race. WE DO REMEMBER (9) settled midfield and couldn't improve when resuming over 1120m at Lismore last time out. Strips fitter and a bit of extra ground should help. POWERFUL DOLPHINS (3) is in the mix on an eight-day back-up. Form nothing to get excited about but the likelihood of a soft lead puts her right in the picture. Market watch on Peter Robl's first starter SKELETON CREW (8) whose trial form has been just fair. The other runners are difficult to recommend.",
